misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes breaking the distance formula into intermediate variables (a, b, c, d) and then applying Math.sqrt to their sum will correctly compute the Euclidean distance.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: There is no conceptual gap here: Java evaluates arithmetic expressions as expected, and using Math.sqrt(c + d) after squaring the coordinate differences correctly implements √((x2−x1)² + (y2−y1)²).
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None; produces correct output (up to normal floating-point precision).
